Additional Legal Information
============================

Privacy Notice
--------------
EchoForge is designed with privacy-first principles. All data processing
occurs locally on the user's machine. No personal data, conversation content,
or usage analytics are transmitted to external servers (except when explicitly
using optional external tool integrations that the user has configured).

Data Responsibility
-------------------
Users are responsible for:
- The content they input into the system
- Compliance with applicable laws and regulations in their jurisdiction
- Proper configuration and security of their installation
- Backup and protection of their local data

AI Model Usage
--------------
EchoForge facilitates the use of AI language models through Ollama and
optionally other providers. Users are responsible for:
- Compliance with the terms of service of any AI model providers they use
- Understanding the capabilities and limitations of AI-generated content
- Not relying solely on AI-generated content for critical decisions
- Verifying information generated by AI models

Content Disclaimer
------------------
The AI agents in EchoForge generate content for educational and exploratory
purposes. The generated content:
- Should not be considered as professional advice (legal, medical, financial, etc.)
- May contain errors, biases, or inaccuracies
- Reflects patterns in training data, not verified facts
- Should be critically evaluated by users

Export Control and Sanctions Compliance
---------------------------------------
Users are responsible for ensuring their use of EchoForge complies with
applicable export control laws and economic sanctions regulations.

Trademark Notice
----------------
"EchoForge" and associated logos (if any) are trademarks of the EchoForge
project. Use of these trademarks must comply with applicable trademark law.

